headlines.description: — Tobias Harris had 37 points and Tyrese Maxey added 21 as the Philadelphia 76ers snapped a three-game losing streak, beating the Sacramento Kings 112-93 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Harris scores 37 points as 76ers, minus Embiid, rout Kings 112-93 to stop 3-game slide

headlines.description: — Buddy Hield and Obi Toppin each scored 18 points and the Indiana Pacers overcame star Tyrese Haliburton's absence with balanced scoring, beating Atlanta 126-108 on Friday night to continue their season dominance over the Hawks.
headlines.shortLinkText: Pacers overcome Haliburton's absence to beat Hawks 126-108

headlines.description: — Fred VanVleet scored 17 points in the second half, including eight in a key fourth-quarter stretch, as the Houston Rockets handed the Detroit Pistons their seventh straight loss, 112-110 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Fred VanVleet's hot 2nd half leads Houston Rockets to comeback victory over Detroit Pistons

headlines.description: — By current NBA standards, this was a throwback: A team won without scoring 100 points.
headlines.shortLinkText: Heat get go-ahead basket from Adebayo, top Magic 99-96 in rare low-scoring game this season

events.name: Golden State Warriors at Chicago Bulls

headlines.description: — Klay Thompson scored 30 points and Stephen Curry scored 15 of his 27 points in the fourth quarter as the Golden State Warriors used a big second-half turnaround to beat the Chicago Bulls 140-131 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Thompson scores 30, lifting Warriors to 140-131 win over Bulls

headlines.description: — Paul George scored a season-high 37 points, Kawhi Leonard added 22 and the Los Angeles Clippers defeated the Memphis Grizzlies 128-119 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: George scores season-high 37 points, Leonard adds 22 as Clippers defeat Grizzlies 128-119

events.name: Portland Trail Blazers at Minnesota Timberwolves

headlines.description: — Rudy Gobert had 24 points and 17 rebounds, Karl-Anthony Towns scored 23 points and the Minnesota Timberwolves cruised to a 116-93 victory over the Portland Trail Blazers on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Timberwolves cruise to 116-93 win over Trail Blazers behind Gobert's 24 points, 17 rebounds

events.name: Charlotte Hornets at San Antonio Spurs

headlines.description: — Victor Wembanyama had 26 points and 11 rebounds and the San Antonio Spurs routed Charlotte 135-99 on Friday night, spoiling Hornets star LaMelo Ball’s return from a 20-game absence.
headlines.shortLinkText: Wembanyama has 26 points and 11 rebounds, Spurs spoil Ball's return to Hornets

headlines.description: — Lauri Markkanen scored 22 points and had nine rebounds to lead the Utah Jazz to a 145-113 victory over the Toronto Raptors on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jazz beat Raptors 145-113 for 7th straight home win

events.name: New Orleans Pelicans at Denver Nuggets

headlines.description: — Nikola Jokic had 27 points, 14 assists and 10 rebounds for his 10th career triple-double against New Orleans in the Denver Nuggets' 125-113 victory over the Pelicans on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Nikola Jokic has another triple-double against New Orleans, Nuggets beat Pelicans 125-113
